While this is only a small fraction of what you can do with cameras in Sequencer, it covers the basics and illustrates how to add cameras to a Level Sequence, move cameras and change between different cameras. You can add keyframes for most of the Post Processing effects from a camera to add film tinting, bloom effects and much more which you can experiment with to reach your desired effect. 


